<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="OSG"></a> OSG </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Steve Clark vs <span class="twikiNewLink">NotreDame<a href="/bin/edit/Accounting/NotreDame?topicparent=Accounting.Minutes2009Jan07" rel="nofollow" title="NotreDame (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> ... this is probably a bug in the <span class="twikiNewLink">SunGridEngine<a href="/bin/edit/Accounting/SunGridEngine?topicparent=Accounting.Minutes2009Jan07" rel="nofollow" title="SunGridEngine (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> probe (takes the common name from the gridmapfile).  The format of the gridmapfile seems to not quite be the one expected by the probe (plus one existing bug we fix but have not release the patch).
</li></ul> 
Chris is following through.
<p />
Keith: We might have an SGE thingy at Fermilab.
<p /> <ul>
<li> Transfer and Storage deployment.
</li></ul> 
<p />
Keith: The Storage probe seems to be login without a certificate into the SE (actually the actual CONTROL interface).  
Brian: OSG has not yet specified the requirement for Storage Allocation.
<p />
Philippe: Do we need the Storage Probe?
<p />
Mine: I will check.
<p />
Philippe/Brian:  However if you need it, the Storage problem probably need to be rewritten.
<p />
Brian/Philippe: Let's get together to write down a list of site we are targeting for early adoption of the probe and/or for Collector install.
<p />
Brian:  Here is a list of sites:
Purdue-RCAC
Nebraska (done)
CIT_CMS_T2
UCSDT2
MIT
UFlorida-PG
GLOW 
